Here are the top 10 horror movies released after 2015, in no particular order:

The Witch (2015) - A family in 1630s New England is torn apart by the forces of witchcraft, black magic, and possession.

Get Out (2017) - A young African-American man visits his white girlfriend's family estate and becomes ensnared in a more sinister reason for the invitation.

Hereditary (2018) - After the matriarch of the Graham family passes away, her daughter and grandchildren begin to unravel cryptic and increasingly terrifying secrets about their ancestry.

A Quiet Place (2018) - In a post-apocalyptic world, a family is forced to live in silence while hiding from creatures that hunt by sound.

It Follows (2014) - A teenage girl is followed by a supernatural entity after a sexual encounter, and must find a way to escape its relentless pursuit.

The Babadook (2014) - A single mother and her son are plagued by a mysterious creature called the Babadook, which manifests as a book that appears in their home.

The Conjuring 2 (2016) - In this sequel to the hit horror film, paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren travel to England to investigate a series of disturbing events.

Us (2019) - A family's vacation turns into a nightmare when they are confronted by their doppelgangers, who are determined to kill them.

Train to Busan (2016) - A group of passengers on a high-speed train from Seoul to Busan must fight for survival against a zombie outbreak.

Midsommar (2019) - A young woman and her friends travel to a remote Swedish village for a festival that occurs once every 90 years, only to discover the seemingly idyllic community hides a dark and violent underbelly.